<TITLE> Sports adviser, NSC chairman greet women's cricket team </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com) -- Sports adviser to caretaker government Tapan Chowdhury greeted members, officials and coaches of the Bangladesh women's cricket team on their becoming unbeaten champions in the Asian Cricket Council (ACC) Women's Cricket Tournament in Malaysia Wednesday. Bangladesh women's team clinched the title beating Nepal eight wickets in the final at Johor Cricket Academy. The sports adviser said it was a great pleasure to see that our women team have become champions in their first participation in any tournament outside the country and that they have to keep it up and continue winning laurels in future. The chairman of National Sports Council (NSC) and Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA), Bangladesh Army Chief General Moeen U Ahmed also hailed the women team for their success in the eight-team tournament in Malaysia. Acting secretary of Youth and Sports Dr M Golam Mostafa Talukdar also welcomed the team's members, officials and coaches for their first-ever success in the ACC Women's Cricket tournament. 
